# badurls/logfile_list
# --------------------
# One absolute Cleanfeed log-file path per line. badurl.py scans these files for
# URL evidence. Blank lines and lines beginning with # are ignored.
#
# Examples for a traditional Cleanfeed installation (disabled):
# /usr/local/news/cleanfeed/log/cf.binary
# /usr/local/news/cleanfeed/log/cf.hosts
# /usr/local/news/cleanfeed/log/cf.path
# /usr/local/news/cleanfeed/log/cf.scoring
# /usr/local/news/cleanfeed/log/emp.fsl
# /usr/local/news/cleanfeed/log/emp.md5
# /usr/local/news/cleanfeed/log/emp.phl
# /usr/local/news/cleanfeed/log/emp.phn
#
# Use only files that exist and are readable by the account running badurl.py.
